1. Create the Repository Locally.

Step 1.
	Download the GIT Tool.
		- Git is the Interface tool used to interact with the GitGub

Website : https://git-scm.com/download/win

file name : Git-2.13.2-64-bit.exe


Step 2.
	Create the folder.

	Ex.

		githubdemo


Step 3.
	Execute the Following Command on GitBash Here.

	> git init

[ Note . When ever we execute above Command Automatically github demo

         Converted as local repository]


Step 2.

	Add the User Credentials to the Repository.

>git config --global user.name "Samba"
>git config --global user.email "samba.pendela@gmail.com"



Step 3.
	Create the Files to the Repository.

>touch sample.js

Step 4.
	Commit the Files to the Repository.

[Note. As a Developer we must commit the files to the Repository]

>git status

	- it will show status of files
	[Note : red color files indicating untracked files]

> git add sample.js	

> git commit

> press "i"

> type "initial commit"

> press "ESC"

> type ":wq"

> press "enter"



From 2nd Commit Onwards we can follow the below commands.
-

>git add .

>git commit -m "Inner Annonymus Functions Created , More Secured!"



4. Create the Branch
	git branch team_one


5. checkout the branch
	git checkout team_one


6. Merge the Branches
	git merge team_one.


7. Working with Cloud Repository With IDE.

Download and Install the NodeJS
-
Website : https://nodejs.org/en/download/

Create the Account with the GitHub
-
website : https://github.com/join

Download Webstrom IDE.
-
Website : https://www.jetbrains.com/webstorm/download/download-thanks.html?platform=windows

Checkout the Code from the Cloud Repository(AngularJS_6AM)
-
https://github.com/ajsnaresh/AJS_Classes.git




Push the Code.
-

ctrl + k


Pull the Code
-

VCS --> Git ---> Pull  ---> AngularJS_6AM ---> Pull.


